WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:02:05.083 --> 00:02:07.251
These are our terms.

3
00:02:07.252 --> 00:02:10.963
One hundred of your
golden dragons.

4
00:02:10.964 --> 00:02:13.757
Per ship?

5
00:02:13.758 --> 00:02:15.092
Per man.

6
00:02:15.093 --> 00:02:17.094
I could not produce such a coin.

7
00:02:17.095 --> 00:02:18.303
even if I wanted to.

8
00:02:18.304 --> 00:02:20.097
Again. you plead poverty.

9
00:02:20.098 --> 00:02:22.975
It is hollow stuff from
the mouth of a Lannister.

10
00:02:22.976 --> 00:02:24.560
Whose very stables
and sculleries

11
00:02:24.561 --> 00:02:26.603
are carved into a
mountain of gold.

12
00:02:26.604 --> 00:02:29.565
And we will need it
before this war is done.

13
00:02:29.566 --> 00:02:32.276
Break the blockade and
it will benefit you.

14
00:02:32.277 --> 00:02:34.236
Do you think that
we lack for buyers

15
00:02:34.237 --> 00:02:36.780
for our tapestries and perfumes?

16
00:02:36.781 --> 00:02:39.074
We sell where we please.

17
00:02:39.075 --> 00:02:40.993
blockade or no.

18
00:02:40.994 --> 00:02:43.829
Essos is as rich as it is vast.

19
00:02:43.830 --> 00:02:48.125
It seems you need us
more than we need you.

20
00:02:51.963 --> 00:02:53.214
The Stepstones.

21
00:02:55.717 --> 00:02:57.968
What of them?

22
00:02:57.969 --> 00:02:59.637
Give us the Stepstones.

23
00:03:00.805 --> 00:03:02.474
A smattering of rocks...

24
00:03:03.308 --> 00:03:06.685
hardly a sacrifice to
the lords of Westeros.

25
00:03:06.686 --> 00:03:11.816
I... Those rocks have been
disputed for a generation.

26
00:03:13.151 --> 00:03:14.319
Your...

27
00:03:15.236 --> 00:03:19.323
pirates have waylaid ships.
taken slaves. cargo...

28
00:03:19.324 --> 00:03:22.034
Give them to us
outright. if you prevail.

29
00:03:22.035 --> 00:03:24.536
and all that will cease.

30
00:03:24.537 --> 00:03:26.288
We will impose a simple tax

31
00:03:26.289 --> 00:03:27.998
on those passing through.

32
00:03:27.999 --> 00:03:30.334
Recoup the losses
we took fighting

33
00:03:30.335 --> 00:03:32.002
- the Velaryon hordes.
- Extortion.

34
00:03:32.003 --> 00:03:34.004
You will drive up the
price of basic goods.

35
00:03:34.005 --> 00:03:37.342
It is better than
starving. surely.

36
00:03:41.012 --> 00:03:44.014
A fleet of warships. then.
sailing at your command.

37
00:03:44.015 --> 00:03:46.183
- They would break the blockade...
- Hm.

38
00:03:46.184 --> 00:03:47.852
And hold the passage.

39
00:03:53.608 --> 00:03:54.859
Very well.

40
00:03:58.697 --> 00:04:01.490
The prince regent may
have me hanged for this.

41
00:04:01.491 --> 00:04:03.492
With the armada we send now.

42
00:04:03.493 --> 00:04:05.869
you can topple the prince regent

43
00:04:05.870 --> 00:04:08.039
and sit the Iron
Throne yourself.

44
00:04:12.377 --> 00:04:16.839
Of Course. there is
one more condition.

45
00:04:19.384 --> 00:04:20.718
I was...

46
00:04:20.719 --> 00:04:23.262
rather set on a bath
and a flagon of wine.

47
00:04:23.263 --> 00:04:24.722
The commander of our fleet

48
00:04:24.723 --> 00:04:26.223
must agree to go with you.

49
00:04:26.224 --> 00:04:29.184
His name is Lohar. The sailors
are fiercely loyal to him.

50
00:04:29.185 --> 00:04:30.686
If. if he does not lead them.

51
00:04:30.687 --> 00:04:32.313
they will not fight.

52
00:04:34.816 --> 00:04:36.067
Very well.

53
00:04:36.735 --> 00:04:39.362
Let us meet this commander then.

54
00:04:50.498 --> 00:04:51.750
Admiral Lohar...

55
00:04:52.917 --> 00:04:55.127
this is Tyland Lannister.

56
00:04:55.128 --> 00:04:57.005
of Casterly Rock.

57
00:04:57.964 --> 00:05:00.425
Well met. Lord Tywin.

58
00:05:01.176 --> 00:05:02.427
Uh...

59
00:05:04.763 --> 00:05:06.765
it's Tyland.

60
00:05:08.600 --> 00:05:10.268
What sort of man are you?

61
00:05:11.686 --> 00:05:14.939
- I beg your pardon?
- A poet...

62
00:05:15.940 --> 00:05:17.150
a philosopher?

63
00:05:17.692 --> 00:05:20.445
I am the master of
ships at King's Landing.

64
00:05:20.945 --> 00:05:24.157
- You're thin.
- But also tall.

65
00:05:26.785 --> 00:05:30.245
I will not sail with a
man who cannot best me.

66
00:05:35.960 --> 00:05:37.504
At. at what?

67
00:06:26.928 --> 00:06:29.014
Some rum wouldn't go amiss.

68
00:06:30.223 --> 00:06:31.683
Your Grace.

69
00:06:32.434 --> 00:06:34.060
Just a little.

70
00:06:42.694 --> 00:06:44.863
You're a good man. Orwyle.

71
00:06:57.542 --> 00:06:58.752
A word. Your Grace?

72
00:07:19.064 --> 00:07:21.941
I must ask you. Your
Grace. to steel yourself.

73
00:07:23.068 --> 00:07:25.235
We must leave King's
Landing. quickly.

74
00:07:25.236 --> 00:07:27.572
and we will not
return for some time.

75
00:07:29.449 --> 00:07:33.952
- What?
- The Pretender has found three new riders for her dragons.

76
00:07:33.953 --> 00:07:37.289
- That's impossible.
- Your brother thought the same.

77
00:07:37.290 --> 00:07:40.209
He flew to challenge
her and was rebuffed.

78
00:07:40.210 --> 00:07:42.253
Fled in terror.
from what I hear.

79
00:07:44.464 --> 00:07:46.383
He deserves no less.

80
00:07:46.591 --> 00:07:50.595
Be that as it may. he has
gone in fury to Sharp Point...

81
00:07:51.262 --> 00:07:53.932
and laid waste to the
whole of the town.

82
00:07:55.308 --> 00:07:57.769
Fucking mad cunt.

83
00:08:00.313 --> 00:08:01.773
She really did it then?

84
00:08:02.524 --> 00:08:04.109
I fear so.

85
00:08:05.777 --> 00:08:08.655
So. what was the fucking
point in all this then?

86
00:08:09.989 --> 00:08:12.282
The gods are cruel. Your Grace.

87
00:08:12.283 --> 00:08:15.786
but I hope you can
see the urgency.

88
00:08:15.787 --> 00:08:20.917
No. no. I am the
king. Why must I run?

89
00:08:21.334 --> 00:08:23.795
Because the prince regent
is going to kill you.

90
00:08:28.133 --> 00:08:29.299
You were in danger before.

91
00:08:29.300 --> 00:08:32.761
and now. he is thwarted
and he is angry.

92
00:08:32.762 --> 00:08:34.179
There is no telling
what he will do.

93
00:08:34.180 --> 00:08:35.848
but we have an opportunity

94
00:08:35.849 --> 00:08:38.893
- while he is away...
- An opportunity to push him out.

95
00:08:39.686 --> 00:08:41.812
Take me to my throne

96
00:08:41.813 --> 00:08:46.150
and once he returns. I shall
take him prisoner... hm?

97
00:08:46.151 --> 00:08:47.569
And what then?

98
00:08:49.029 --> 00:08:51.488
When Rhaenyra descends on
you with her seven dragons.

99
00:08:51.489 --> 00:08:53.825
and you. without
Vhagar. what then?

100
00:08:55.535 --> 00:08:56.536
W...

101
00:08:57.662 --> 00:08:58.705
Uh...

102
00:09:05.378 --> 00:09:07.004
I have. over the years.

103
00:09:07.005 --> 00:09:09.506
in anticipation of
little bumps in the road.

104
00:09:09.507 --> 00:09:12.134
moved the greater part of
Harrenhal's gold reserves

105
00:09:12.135 --> 00:09:14.219
to the Iron Bank in Braavos.

106
00:09:14.220 --> 00:09:16.847
We can live... well

107
00:09:16.848 --> 00:09:20.351
and remain until what
is coming has passed.

108
00:09:23.021 --> 00:09:26.357
Y... You want to
take me to Essos

109
00:09:26.358 --> 00:09:28.360
to live with the goatfuckers.

110
00:09:29.569 --> 00:09:31.571
It's best to live. I think.

111
00:09:31.905 --> 00:09:34.199
- However you do it.
- Is it?

112
00:09:36.076 --> 00:09:38.078
My dragon is dead.

113
00:09:38.703 --> 00:09:40.746
I am burnt...

114
00:09:40.747 --> 00:09:44.417
and disgusting... and alone.

115
00:09:45.251 --> 00:09:46.711
And I'm a cripple.

116
00:09:50.423 --> 00:09:51.882
You are not alone.

117
00:09:51.883 --> 00:09:54.843
My cock is destroyed.
did they tell you that?

118
00:09:54.844 --> 00:09:58.722
Yeah. It burst into flames
like a sausage on the spit.

119
00:09:58.723 --> 00:10:00.265
Do not despair. Your Grace.

120
00:10:00.266 --> 00:10:02.227
There are better days ahead.

121
00:10:02.602 --> 00:10:05.104
Let your brother
and the Pretender

122
00:10:05.105 --> 00:10:08.190
destroy themselves in
blood and bitterness.

123
00:10:08.191 --> 00:10:09.608
When they are spent.

124
00:10:09.609 --> 00:10:11.110
and their armies in tatters.

125
00:10:11.111 --> 00:10:12.611
we will return.

126
00:10:12.612 --> 00:10:16.031
and the people will
rise up to meet us.

127
00:10:16.032 --> 00:10:19.076
I can't even piss without
it running down my leg.

128
00:10:19.077 --> 00:10:23.748
They will be tired of
endless deprivation and fear.

129
00:10:25.125 --> 00:10:27.752
They will hail the
returning king...

130
00:10:28.420 --> 00:10:31.256
his father's true heir.

131
00:10:32.674 --> 00:10:35.551
Aegon the Victorious...

132
00:10:35.552 --> 00:10:37.595
risen from the ashes.

133
00:10:38.638 --> 00:10:40.640
Aegon the Peacemaker.

134
00:10:43.685 --> 00:10:45.687
Aegon the Rebuilder.

135
00:10:49.232 --> 00:10:51.860
Aegon. the Realm's Delight.

136
00:11:39.657 --> 00:11:42.659
This is more like it.
Hugh. don't you think?

137
00:11:42.660 --> 00:11:44.995
We're meant to be at the training
yards learnin' the commands.

138
00:11:44.996 --> 00:11:46.663
Yeah. and I will go.

139
00:11:46.664 --> 00:11:50.042
but surely they'd not deny
me my pleasure after so long.

140
00:11:50.043 --> 00:11:52.712
I may never eat fish again.

141
00:11:53.588 --> 00:11:55.298
What are you doing here?

142
00:11:55.840 --> 00:11:57.341
Remove your feet from the table.

143
00:11:57.342 --> 00:11:59.134
- I'd rather not.
- Ulf.

144
00:11:59.135 --> 00:12:01.845
It's not up to you... Ulf.

145
00:12:01.846 --> 00:12:04.973
Who's it up to then... boy?

146
00:12:04.974 --> 00:12:09.186
He is the prince. Ulf.
Prince Jacaerys Velaryon.

147
00:12:09.187 --> 00:12:12.981
Prince Jacaerys
Velaryon. Right here.

148
00:12:12.982 --> 00:12:14.566
Who'd have thought it?

149
00:12:14.567 --> 00:12:16.360
He lives here.

150
00:12:16.361 --> 00:12:17.946
I'll have an apology from you.

151
00:12:18.738 --> 00:12:21.198
Ah! The young prince!

152
00:12:21.199 --> 00:12:23.034
And look at that hair.

153
00:12:24.869 --> 00:12:27.538
As dark as they say.

154
00:12:27.539 --> 00:12:30.000
Let them tell us we don't
have Targaryen blood. eh?

155
00:12:30.709 --> 00:12:34.503
- My mother is the queen and...
- Dragonriders both.

156
00:12:34.504 --> 00:12:37.840
You and I... cut
from the same cloth.

157
00:12:37.841 --> 00:12:40.885
It is a sacred inheritance
of which you know nothing.

158
00:12:41.636 --> 00:12:43.512
Forgive him. my prince.

159
00:12:43.513 --> 00:12:46.390
He is not much used to
the manners of court.

160
00:12:46.391 --> 00:12:48.225
Or any manners at all. I'd say.

161
00:12:48.226 --> 00:12:51.396
Do you know what has
happened this last hour. hm?

162
00:12:52.564 --> 00:12:54.189
The so-called prince regent

163
00:12:54.190 --> 00:12:56.066
has burned Sharp Point
down to its stones.

164
00:12:56.067 --> 00:12:58.193
Thousands of its
folk dead or lost.

165
00:12:58.194 --> 00:12:59.863
Its harbor in ashes.

166
00:13:01.072 --> 00:13:03.658
Will you prepare to
face such an enemy?

167
00:13:05.243 --> 00:13:08.078
Or will you stay here
and make yourself easy?

168
00:13:08.079 --> 00:13:10.372
If you hinder our efforts

169
00:13:10.373 --> 00:13:12.750
through sloth or unreadiness.

170
00:13:12.751 --> 00:13:14.084
I will see you hanged.

171
00:13:14.085 --> 00:13:17.379
and your body fed to
the dogs in the street.

172
00:13:17.380 --> 00:13:20.425
I-I meant no
disrespect. my prince.

173
00:13:36.900 --> 00:13:39.276
The new riders are a boon to us.

174
00:13:39.277 --> 00:13:41.653
but now the deed is done.

175
00:13:41.654 --> 00:13:44.782
I cannot erase my doubts.

176
00:13:44.783 --> 00:13:46.450
We know little of who they are.

177
00:13:46.451 --> 00:13:49.328
and what is the strength
of their character.

178
00:13:49.329 --> 00:13:51.456
Addam of Hull. at
least. is known to you.

179
00:13:52.874 --> 00:13:55.125
He's a shipwright in my employ.

180
00:13:55.126 --> 00:13:58.796
and it is reported to me that
he is a man of integrity.

181
00:13:58.797 --> 00:14:03.801
I've had little to do
with him... to my regret.

182
00:14:03.802 --> 00:14:06.261
But the beasts
have been claimed.

183
00:14:06.262 --> 00:14:08.681
You now have a great advantage.

184
00:14:08.682 --> 00:14:10.849
You must strike. quickly.

185
00:14:10.850 --> 00:14:13.019
while the prince regent
mulls his next action.

186
00:14:14.646 --> 00:14:17.691
I had hoped my advantage
may be in deterrence.

187
00:14:18.858 --> 00:14:20.651
Vhagar has ever been
our foremost threat.

188
00:14:20.652 --> 00:14:22.653
and she is now overmatched.

189
00:14:22.654 --> 00:14:24.321
Vhagar is not his only dragon.

190
00:14:24.322 --> 00:14:26.156
W... The third
brother is untested.

191
00:14:26.157 --> 00:14:27.616
has never left Oldtown.

192
00:14:27.617 --> 00:14:29.660
and his dragon is
younger than Vermax.

193
00:14:29.661 --> 00:14:31.328
But a dragon nonetheless.

194
00:14:31.329 --> 00:14:33.206
And you forget another.

195
00:14:34.916 --> 00:14:36.167
Helaena?

196
00:14:36.668 --> 00:14:39.044
She does not ride. She
has no taste for it.

197
00:14:39.045 --> 00:14:41.338
She may yet be compelled.

198
00:14:41.339 --> 00:14:43.215
- And her dragon...
- Dreamfyre.

199
00:14:43.216 --> 00:14:45.510
hatched when the
Conqueror was king.

200
00:14:46.594 --> 00:14:48.512
She is formidable.

201
00:14:48.513 --> 00:14:50.765
Still. Helaena is no warrior.

202
00:14:53.935 --> 00:14:56.353
Aemond thought
himself invincible.

203
00:14:56.354 --> 00:14:58.273
He has now discovered he is not.

204
00:14:59.024 --> 00:15:01.276
He'll be angry. desperate.

205
00:15:01.860 --> 00:15:04.069
He will not stop at
burning Sharp Point.

206
00:15:04.070 --> 00:15:06.364
and he will not be denied.

207
00:15:07.073 --> 00:15:08.408
You speak truly...

208
00:15:09.617 --> 00:15:11.326
though I wish it was not so.

209
00:15:16.249 --> 00:15:17.625
How goes the <i>Sea Snake?</i>

210
00:15:19.252 --> 00:15:20.879
Better than new.

211
00:15:21.755 --> 00:15:23.798
We'll rejoin the
blockade on the morrow.

212
00:15:24.215 --> 00:15:27.552
Let our foes beware. be
they Lannister or Greyjoy.

213
00:15:29.054 --> 00:15:32.724
But... my ship is no
longer the <i>Sea Snake.</i>

214
00:15:33.141 --> 00:15:35.727
She was a testament
to my own glory.

215
00:15:36.644 --> 00:15:38.646
I've given her a new name.

216
00:15:40.982 --> 00:15:43.234
<i>The Queen Who Never Was.</i>

217
00:15:45.737 --> 00:15:46.905
Corlys...

218
00:15:48.073 --> 00:15:49.741
I thank you.

219
00:15:53.953 --> 00:15:57.582
What I do now... I do for her.

220
00:16:00.251 --> 00:16:02.294
Your Grace. you are ready.

221
00:16:02.295 --> 00:16:05.798
You have six dragons
under your banner.

222
00:16:05.799 --> 00:16:08.217
My ships sail at your command.

223
00:16:08.218 --> 00:16:09.719
and my men serve you.

224
00:16:10.428 --> 00:16:12.429
But the Lannisters are marching.

225
00:16:12.430 --> 00:16:13.973
and the Hightowers from Oldtown.

226
00:16:15.100 --> 00:16:19.311
You must crush this
beast at its head

227
00:16:19.312 --> 00:16:21.773
and before too many
days have flown.

228
00:16:25.110 --> 00:16:27.152
There is. of course...

229
00:16:27.153 --> 00:16:30.615
another player that
has yet to be revealed.

230
00:16:32.617 --> 00:16:34.660
Ah. Your Grace. a word.

231
00:16:34.661 --> 00:16:38.122
It seems the sheep on our
land has been sold upriver.

232
00:16:38.123 --> 00:16:40.958
My vassals have sent a
drove of swine instead.

233
00:16:40.959 --> 00:16:42.751
Dragons do eat pigs. I assume?

234
00:16:42.752 --> 00:16:45.129
Caraxes prefers them.
How goes your muster?

235
00:16:45.130 --> 00:16:46.630
We'll be ready to march
in two days' time.

236
00:16:46.631 --> 00:16:48.924
- See to those pigs.
- At once. Your Grace.

237
00:16:48.925 --> 00:16:52.678
Your Grace... Ser Alfred
Broome has come to see you.

238
00:16:52.679 --> 00:16:55.264
Interesting.

239
00:16:55.265 --> 00:16:57.266
I am sent as an
emissary from the queen.

240
00:16:57.267 --> 00:16:59.685
to ascertain your movements
and your intentions.

241
00:16:59.686 --> 00:17:00.978
You've arrived just in time

242
00:17:00.979 --> 00:17:03.605
to see my new army. Broome.

243
00:17:03.606 --> 00:17:05.315
What do you think of it?

244
00:17:05.316 --> 00:17:07.109
It's very large.

245
00:17:09.320 --> 00:17:11.364
Lannister hesitates.

246
00:17:11.823 --> 00:17:14.533
I aim to march on King's
Landing before he can catch me.

247
00:17:14.534 --> 00:17:17.203
May I have a word in
private. Your Grace?

248
00:17:21.875 --> 00:17:23.959
I would speak honestly with you.

249
00:17:23.960 --> 00:17:25.502
I'd expect nothing less.

250
00:17:25.503 --> 00:17:28.339
I was faithful to the
king. your brother.

251
00:17:28.340 --> 00:17:30.966
I pledged my banners
to Rhaenyra. his heir.

252
00:17:30.967 --> 00:17:32.843
I will never serve the usurpers

253
00:17:32.844 --> 00:17:34.720
or the whelps of Oldtown.

254
00:17:34.721 --> 00:17:36.805
but there are battles
to be fought...

255
00:17:36.806 --> 00:17:39.434
- Traitor.
- And in times like this...

256
00:17:42.520 --> 00:17:44.189
Did you hear something?

257
00:17:46.107 --> 00:17:48.735
This place will have
you barking at the moon.

258
00:17:51.738 --> 00:17:53.530
While you have mustered an army.

259
00:17:53.531 --> 00:17:55.240
Rhaenyra has faltered...

260
00:17:55.241 --> 00:17:57.076
turning aside from our judgment.

261
00:17:57.077 --> 00:17:59.495
and taking a course. I
myself. deem reckless.

262
00:17:59.496 --> 00:18:03.499
Rhaenyra will chart her own
course. for good or ill.

263
00:18:03.500 --> 00:18:05.460
But you are a leader of men.

264
00:18:06.795 --> 00:18:09.254
If you declare yourself.

265
00:18:09.255 --> 00:18:11.216
your lords will follow you.

266
00:18:11.716 --> 00:18:14.552
I never took you
for a turncloak...

267
00:18:15.553 --> 00:18:17.138
Ser Alfred.

268
00:18:20.058 --> 00:18:22.227
Rhaenyra's intentions are good.

269
00:18:24.062 --> 00:18:27.649
But what we need.
in this moment...

270
00:18:29.317 --> 00:18:30.735
is a king.

271
00:18:57.595 --> 00:18:59.304
<i>It appears that the Pretender</i>

272
00:18:59.305 --> 00:19:01.223
sent boats to collect
those among the smallfolk

273
00:19:01.224 --> 00:19:03.767
who believed they had any
drop of Targaryen blood.

274
00:19:03.768 --> 00:19:05.894
Deception and subterfuge.

275
00:19:05.895 --> 00:19:09.064
Cowards. all of them. Put
an end to this madness.

276
00:19:09.065 --> 00:19:12.317
Let no vessel come or go from our
harbor without our inspection.

277
00:19:12.318 --> 00:19:14.653
This will hinder the work
of the fishing boats.

278
00:19:14.654 --> 00:19:16.780
The people depend on
them for sustenance.

279
00:19:16.781 --> 00:19:18.449
They will need no sustenance

280
00:19:18.450 --> 00:19:20.826
if they are slaughtered
by the enemy.

281
00:19:20.827 --> 00:19:23.121
We must all make our sacrifices.

282
00:19:25.665 --> 00:19:28.000
<i>Why does everybody hate us?</i>

283
00:19:28.001 --> 00:19:30.002
They're unhappy...

284
00:19:30.003 --> 00:19:32.464
and unhappy people look
for someone to hate.

285
00:19:36.134 --> 00:19:38.135
We didn't order the blockade.

286
00:19:38.136 --> 00:19:41.222
No. but we are the crown. so
they expect us to break it.

287
00:19:42.557 --> 00:19:43.808
Drink this.

288
00:19:50.982 --> 00:19:53.651
I was happier
before I was queen.

289
00:20:00.200 --> 00:20:02.660
What would you think
about leaving this place?

290
00:20:11.503 --> 00:20:13.504
Where would I go?

291
00:20:19.761 --> 00:20:21.303
The prince regent. Your Grace.

292
00:20:21.304 --> 00:20:24.015
Helaena. Here you are. Mother.

293
00:20:26.768 --> 00:20:30.187
- I was just. just going to bed.
- The crown has need of your service.

294
00:20:30.188 --> 00:20:32.731
- Now?
- The Pretender has raised new riders against us.

295
00:20:32.732 --> 00:20:35.402
and we must answer in kind.

296
00:20:36.611 --> 00:20:38.487
I need you to fly with
Dreamfyre to battle.

297
00:20:38.488 --> 00:20:40.364
- Aemond.
- I do not wish to fight.

298
00:20:40.365 --> 00:20:42.658
Our wishes must take
second place now

299
00:20:42.659 --> 00:20:45.286
to what is necessary
to preserve the throne.

300
00:20:46.204 --> 00:20:48.206
I won't burn anyone.

301
00:20:50.250 --> 00:20:51.709
It isn't a question.

302
00:20:51.710 --> 00:20:53.419
- Aemond.
- They have defiled our birthright.

303
00:20:53.420 --> 00:20:55.170
- made commoners into dragonlords!
- Ow. ow!

304
00:20:55.171 --> 00:20:56.672
- Aemond! Aemond!
- It is a sin and must be punished!

305
00:20:56.673 --> 00:20:58.507
- May I remind you your sister is still the queen?
- Ow!

306
00:20:58.508 --> 00:21:00.384
As you were once!
And you see now

307
00:21:00.385 --> 00:21:02.052
what is the consequence
of your weakness!

308
00:21:02.053 --> 00:21:04.221
We are in peril today
more than yesterday!

309
00:21:04.222 --> 00:21:06.849
Was it peril that moved you to
burn the town of Sharp Point?

310
00:21:06.850 --> 00:21:09.518
Peril or basest fury at
your own humiliation?

311
00:21:09.519 --> 00:21:11.228
Ow!

312
00:21:11.229 --> 00:21:12.730
You wish to rule
the Seven Kingdoms.

313
00:21:12.731 --> 00:21:15.107
but you rain ruin and
death upon its smallfolk

314
00:21:15.108 --> 00:21:17.276
when you've been insulted

315
00:21:17.277 --> 00:21:19.236
because it makes you feel strong

316
00:21:19.237 --> 00:21:21.113
and now you seek to
corrupt your sister.

317
00:21:21.114 --> 00:21:23.407
of all our line. the
gentlest and most deserving

318
00:21:23.408 --> 00:21:24.908
- of your protection.
- And who will protect her

319
00:21:24.909 --> 00:21:26.201
if she cannot protect herself?

320
00:21:26.202 --> 00:21:27.619
And who will she be if
her mind is broken?!

321
00:21:27.620 --> 00:21:29.747
'Tis no longer our rule
that is threatened.

322
00:21:29.748 --> 00:21:31.040
our very lives.

323
00:21:31.041 --> 00:21:32.961
- Would you not have us prevail?
- Not like this.

324
00:21:36.588 --> 00:21:38.423
Not like this!

325
00:21:55.315 --> 00:21:56.775
Grand Maester
Orwyle: Your Grace.

326
00:21:57.525 --> 00:21:58.777
Grand Maester.

327
00:22:00.153 --> 00:22:02.364
I must again request
your assistance.

328
00:22:03.114 --> 00:22:04.783
I need passage.

329
00:22:05.658 --> 00:22:07.535
And your discretion.

330
00:22:19.464 --> 00:22:22.300
Do you think nothing
of your oath...

331
00:22:24.302 --> 00:22:25.720
Lord Commander?

332
00:22:27.889 --> 00:22:30.016
I think of nothing
else. my lord.

333
00:22:31.351 --> 00:22:33.686
Steward's son from Dorne

334
00:22:33.687 --> 00:22:36.356
fucking the queen of
the Seven Kingdoms.

335
00:22:38.400 --> 00:22:40.984
Former queen.

336
00:22:40.985 --> 00:22:42.986
She has broken no oath.
for all I may have done.

337
00:22:42.987 --> 00:22:45.823
- I could send you to the Wall.
- You could.

338
00:22:45.824 --> 00:22:48.910
Stain the Hightower
name for a generation.

339
00:22:49.327 --> 00:22:52.163
- King's mother and his Hand.
- She is my sister.

340
00:22:55.041 --> 00:22:57.002
She saved my life.

341
00:22:57.919 --> 00:22:59.378
Twice.

342
00:22:59.379 --> 00:23:02.173
Once from the headsman's
axe and once from myself.

343
00:23:05.844 --> 00:23:08.430
Since then. she has been
the beacon I follow.

344
00:23:18.064 --> 00:23:20.692
Do not think I have
no shame in me. ser.

345
00:23:22.068 --> 00:23:24.863
Desire for women has brought
me grief after grief.

346
00:23:25.405 --> 00:23:29.366
Then resist it.

347
00:23:29.367 --> 00:23:31.201
Oh. would that it
were so simple.

348
00:23:31.202 --> 00:23:33.913
Your brothers in the
Kingsguard find a way.

349
00:23:37.083 --> 00:23:38.543
Do they?

350
00:23:40.253 --> 00:23:41.921
Mm. perhaps they do.

351
00:23:43.882 --> 00:23:46.301
Or perhaps all
men are corrupt...

352
00:23:48.053 --> 00:23:50.472
and true honor is a mist

353
00:23:51.389 --> 00:23:52.891
that melts in the morning.

354
00:23:55.477 --> 00:23:58.062
That is a bleak philosophy.

355
00:23:58.063 --> 00:23:59.939
I have no philosophy.

356
00:24:01.274 --> 00:24:03.485
Or rather. my
philosophy was this.

357
00:24:05.904 --> 00:24:07.237
To protect the righteous

358
00:24:07.238 --> 00:24:09.657
and dispense
justice on the rest.

359
00:24:11.785 --> 00:24:12.994
But now...

360
00:24:16.331 --> 00:24:18.166
You saw what I saw.

361
00:24:23.463 --> 00:24:27.467
The dragons dance. and men are
like dust under their feet.

362
00:24:31.096 --> 00:24:34.598
And all our fine thoughts.
all our... endeavors

363
00:24:34.599 --> 00:24:36.267
are as nothing.

364
00:24:42.148 --> 00:24:44.984
We march now toward
our annihilation.

365
00:24:51.449 --> 00:24:53.993
To die will be a kind of relief.

366
00:24:58.623 --> 00:25:00.041
Don't you think?

367
00:26:39.641 --> 00:26:42.893
You have impressed
me. Lord Tyman.

368
00:26:42.894 --> 00:26:46.397
King's Landing has sent a
most doughty ambassador.

369
00:26:49.484 --> 00:26:55.239
I hope... you will testify to
the worth of the ambassador...

370
00:26:55.240 --> 00:26:59.034
by agreeing to his
most humble request.

371
00:26:59.035 --> 00:27:02.080
I will most certainly
consider it.

372
00:27:09.462 --> 00:27:11.256
After dinner.

373
00:27:15.635 --> 00:27:18.262
Have you ever eaten the
flesh of your enemies?

374
00:27:18.263 --> 00:27:19.931
What?

375
00:27:22.267 --> 00:27:25.270
I have not and I would not.

376
00:27:26.938 --> 00:27:31.359
So you reject the
hospitality of my house.

377
00:27:42.162 --> 00:27:43.621
A jest. my lord.

378
00:27:44.956 --> 00:27:47.792
What do you take me for?

379
00:27:50.795 --> 00:27:52.005
A jest!

380
00:27:53.048 --> 00:27:54.299
Come.

381
00:28:09.147 --> 00:28:11.566
It does not befit
a prince to pout.

382
00:28:13.360 --> 00:28:14.985
I'm not pouting.

383
00:28:14.986 --> 00:28:16.404
What would you call it. then?

384
00:28:18.907 --> 00:28:22.160
- I'm reading.
- While your mother waits?

385
00:28:25.997 --> 00:28:27.665
You're angry.

386
00:28:30.835 --> 00:28:32.044
Aren't you?

387
00:28:32.045 --> 00:28:33.546
I don't see what
good it would do.

388
00:28:34.839 --> 00:28:37.299
They are an insult to us.

389
00:28:37.300 --> 00:28:39.218
To what makes us Targaryens.

390
00:28:39.219 --> 00:28:41.178
If any common lout
can ride a dragon.

391
00:28:41.179 --> 00:28:44.015
- then...
- That does not make me common. Or you.

392
00:28:45.433 --> 00:28:48.060
- You know what I am.
- I don't care.

393
00:28:48.061 --> 00:28:50.187
You are the crown prince.

394
00:28:50.188 --> 00:28:51.980
the son of the rightful queen.

395
00:28:51.981 --> 00:28:53.524
and here you are sulking

396
00:28:53.525 --> 00:28:55.025
because you believe that
if not for the dragon

397
00:28:55.026 --> 00:28:56.694
or the trappings
of your station.

398
00:28:56.695 --> 00:28:58.529
that you are nothing.

399
00:28:58.530 --> 00:29:01.156
Do you believe that you
are the first noble heir

400
00:29:01.157 --> 00:29:03.493
who was not sired
by his noble father?

401
00:29:04.119 --> 00:29:06.537
Such is the way of
the world. Jace.

402
00:29:06.538 --> 00:29:09.665
and in resenting it. you
only diminish yourself.

403
00:29:09.666 --> 00:29:11.292
Easy enough to say.

404
00:29:11.793 --> 00:29:14.336
I've heard the whispers
the whole of my life.

405
00:29:14.337 --> 00:29:16.588
Then prove to them
that you are worthy.

406
00:29:16.589 --> 00:29:18.215
Get up and take your place

407
00:29:18.216 --> 00:29:19.592
by your mother's side.

408
00:29:44.284 --> 00:29:47.286
♪ Here come my lads.
my comely boys ♪

409
00:29:47.287 --> 00:29:49.872
♪ And split your sacks ashore ♪

410
00:29:49.873 --> 00:29:53.083
♪ For you'll be
sail-sailing many days ♪

411
00:29:53.084 --> 00:29:54.711
♪ Afore you get some more ♪

412
00:29:55.420 --> 00:29:58.089
♪ So grease the mast
and send it up ♪

413
00:29:59.424 --> 00:30:01.593
♪ Betwixt the wind and water ♪

414
00:30:02.302 --> 00:30:04.554
♪ Hoist. me lads.
and hoist again ♪

415
00:30:05.263 --> 00:30:08.433
♪ Salute the
captain's daughter ♪

416
00:30:12.771 --> 00:30:14.773
Well done. Lord Tyrod!

417
00:30:23.490 --> 00:30:26.326
Good song. well delivered.

418
00:30:29.454 --> 00:30:31.623
It's Tyland.

419
00:30:33.208 --> 00:30:36.251
You have proven yourself
most accommodating.

420
00:30:36.252 --> 00:30:39.463
And more accomplished than one
would think. to look at you.

421
00:30:39.464 --> 00:30:42.509
Hm. Well... Hm.

422
00:30:44.844 --> 00:30:48.056
I will be pleased to
sail at your side.

423
00:30:49.974 --> 00:30:52.394
- Oh.
- And my captains with me.

424
00:31:00.151 --> 00:31:03.028
To the Gullet on the morrow!

425
00:31:09.494 --> 00:31:11.662
And let the Sea Snake

426
00:31:11.663 --> 00:31:14.164
rue the day we meet again.

427
00:31:18.545 --> 00:31:20.879
Ya! My king will
be well pleased.

428
00:31:20.880 --> 00:31:22.506
To friendship!

429
00:31:36.938 --> 00:31:38.356
It is late.

430
00:31:41.568 --> 00:31:43.068
Oh!

431
00:31:43.069 --> 00:31:44.738
Before you go...

432
00:31:45.447 --> 00:31:46.697
Lord Tyland.

433
00:31:46.698 --> 00:31:47.699
Mm.

434
00:31:49.242 --> 00:31:50.868
You are a handsome man.

435
00:31:50.869 --> 00:31:56.541
and you have proven
your worth and virility.

436
00:31:58.710 --> 00:32:00.712
I wish to have children by you.

437
00:32:05.133 --> 00:32:08.761
You. you... You want me to...

438
00:32:08.762 --> 00:32:10.055
Indeed.

439
00:32:12.724 --> 00:32:14.768
I want you to fuck my wives.

440
00:32:19.439 --> 00:32:22.650
How many wives do you have?

441
00:32:26.404 --> 00:32:28.990
More wine here!

442
00:32:30.742 --> 00:32:32.744
Taming a dragon is thirsty work.

443
00:32:37.749 --> 00:32:40.418
Oh. and some more of
these little birds.

444
00:32:47.342 --> 00:32:48.760
A toast.

445
00:32:50.512 --> 00:32:52.764
To our new riders.

446
00:32:53.932 --> 00:32:56.266
The three of you are
not of noble birth.

447
00:32:56.267 --> 00:32:59.311
but you have done a thing
never dreamed of before now.

448
00:33:11.116 --> 00:33:14.576
I have entrusted you with a
power only few have known.

449
00:33:14.577 --> 00:33:18.164
And I charge you to take it
up with fealty and respect.

450
00:33:18.998 --> 00:33:22.002
Serve me well. and I will
make you knights of the realm.

451
00:33:23.044 --> 00:33:25.755
Huh? What do you
think of that. boys?

452
00:33:26.297 --> 00:33:28.966
We'll be knights...
just like that.

453
00:33:28.967 --> 00:33:31.011
We will not fail you. my queen.

454
00:33:32.846 --> 00:33:34.472
What must we do?

455
00:33:37.058 --> 00:33:40.061
I had thought the mere fact of
you might stay the enemy's hand.

456
00:33:41.980 --> 00:33:43.773
But Lord Corlys is right.

457
00:33:44.149 --> 00:33:47.360
We must strike while we
have the advantage...

458
00:33:48.028 --> 00:33:49.279
and end this war.

459
00:33:49.654 --> 00:33:52.323
Learn your beasts
and your commands.

460
00:33:52.824 --> 00:33:54.451
You will fly in two days' time.

461
00:33:55.326 --> 00:33:58.954
The strongholds of the usurper.
Oldtown and Lannisport.

462
00:33:58.955 --> 00:34:02.625
and their armies.
all must be subdued.

463
00:34:03.376 --> 00:34:06.211
Alone. without allies. he will
have no choice but to surrender.

464
00:34:06.212 --> 00:34:08.672
You wish for us
to kill innocents.

465
00:34:08.673 --> 00:34:10.717
- And so many.
- It is hard...

466
00:34:11.760 --> 00:34:13.635
but it cannot be helped.

467
00:34:18.516 --> 00:34:20.560
We must break the
will of our enemy...

468
00:34:21.561 --> 00:34:22.895
or more will die in a struggle

469
00:34:22.896 --> 00:34:24.396
that stretches on without end.

470
00:34:24.397 --> 00:34:25.899
What about Vhagar?

471
00:34:27.192 --> 00:34:31.780
She is fearsome...
but she is one dragon.

472
00:34:33.198 --> 00:34:35.199
The prince regent cannot
defend against all of us.

473
00:34:35.200 --> 00:34:38.994
I'll take him on myself.
Silverwing's a goer. she is.

474
00:34:38.995 --> 00:34:41.206
- We're afraid of nothing.
- Hm.

475
00:34:41.706 --> 00:34:44.166
- Even if you are.
- There will be time enough

476
00:34:44.167 --> 00:34:45.794
to see which one
of us is a coward.

477
00:34:47.087 --> 00:34:49.422
I said more of
these little birds!

478
00:34:51.216 --> 00:34:55.387
A knight will comport himself
with grace at the queen's table.

479
00:34:55.804 --> 00:34:57.138
Best make me a knight. then.

480
00:35:01.476 --> 00:35:03.311
You forget yourself...

481
00:35:04.938 --> 00:35:06.147
friend.

482
00:35:10.527 --> 00:35:12.570
A sense of humor
would do you all good.

483
00:35:23.748 --> 00:35:26.835
There is a message from
Harrenhal. Your Grace.

484
00:35:33.299 --> 00:35:34.550
Daemon?

485
00:35:34.551 --> 00:35:37.761
The castellan. Ser Simon Strong.

486
00:35:37.762 --> 00:35:40.597
Daemon has raised his army...

487
00:35:40.598 --> 00:35:43.601
but Ser Simon fears treachery.

488
00:35:46.938 --> 00:35:48.773
I will not allow it.

489
00:35:50.859 --> 00:35:51.860
Addam...

490
00:35:53.111 --> 00:35:54.279
come with me.

491
00:36:00.118 --> 00:36:01.286
Thank you.

492
00:36:02.620 --> 00:36:03.621
Birds.

493
00:36:25.310 --> 00:36:27.354
Do you never sleep. witch?

494
00:36:32.317 --> 00:36:34.402
I'm goin' to the godswood.

495
00:37:12.190 --> 00:37:15.193
When you came here.
you were a closed fist.

496
00:37:17.696 --> 00:37:21.366
You wished to bend the
world to your will.

497
00:37:23.952 --> 00:37:26.662
But you've discovered.
I think. that...

498
00:37:26.663 --> 00:37:29.290
this world will not be governed.

499
00:37:35.797 --> 00:37:39.217
There are omens here
for those who seek them.

500
00:37:42.679 --> 00:37:44.430
You do not scoff?

501
00:37:44.431 --> 00:37:47.892
I'm no longer inclined to.

502
00:37:49.102 --> 00:37:51.103
I'm pleased to hear it.

503
00:38:02.782 --> 00:38:06.286
Do you wish. then. to
learn what is given to you?

504
00:38:14.627 --> 00:38:16.628
All your life. you
have sought to command

505
00:38:16.629 --> 00:38:18.298
your own fate.

506
00:38:22.886 --> 00:38:25.095
But today you are ready.

507
00:39:48.596 --> 00:39:51.599
It's all a story...

508
00:39:59.858 --> 00:40:02.527
and you are but one part in it.

509
00:40:04.404 --> 00:40:06.655
You know your part.

510
00:40:16.708 --> 00:40:19.543
<i>You know what you must do.</i>

511
00:40:27.719 --> 00:40:28.928
Sister.

512
00:40:29.721 --> 00:40:31.597
We share the same blood.

513
00:40:31.598 --> 00:40:32.891
you and I.

514
00:40:33.808 --> 00:40:36.644
I know you wish
no harm to anyone.

515
00:40:38.938 --> 00:40:41.273
But in a time like this.

516
00:40:41.274 --> 00:40:43.943
when the good of the
realm depends on us...

517
00:40:47.072 --> 00:40:50.366
Our mother is not a dragonrider.

518
00:40:50.367 --> 00:40:52.368
She cannot understand

519
00:40:52.369 --> 00:40:55.413
that you and I have
a truer call to heed.

520
00:41:00.126 --> 00:41:01.753
Come with me...

521
00:41:02.962 --> 00:41:04.422
to Harrenhal?

522
00:41:06.424 --> 00:41:09.427
We will lay waste to
Daemon and his army.

523
00:41:10.261 --> 00:41:15.391
Let our enemy see that we will
answer outrage with outrage.

524
00:41:15.392 --> 00:41:17.435
And if I refuse?

525
00:41:20.355 --> 00:41:22.982
Will you burn me
as you did Aegon?

526
00:41:27.028 --> 00:41:29.656
- That is a lie.
- I saw it.

527
00:41:33.368 --> 00:41:37.163
You burned him and
you let him fall.

528
00:41:41.167 --> 00:41:43.169
What you say is treason.

529
00:41:45.630 --> 00:41:48.008
Aegon will be king again.

530
00:41:51.136 --> 00:41:53.513
He's yet to see victory.

531
00:41:54.639 --> 00:41:57.225
He sits on a wooden throne.

532
00:41:57.976 --> 00:41:59.394
And you...

533
00:42:03.898 --> 00:42:05.900
you'll be dead.

534
00:42:08.653 --> 00:42:11.488
You were swallowed
up in the God's Eye.

535
00:42:11.489 --> 00:42:13.324
and you were never seen again.

536
00:42:18.705 --> 00:42:22.207
I could have you killed.

537
00:42:22.208 --> 00:42:24.878
It wouldn't change anything.

538
00:43:45.500 --> 00:43:48.544
I am the castellan. Ser
Simon Strong. Your Grace.

539
00:43:48.545 --> 00:43:49.754
Well met.

540
00:43:50.755 --> 00:43:52.756
Welcome to Harrenhal. my queen.

541
00:43:52.757 --> 00:43:54.425
I did not think to
see you here yourself.

542
00:43:54.426 --> 00:43:57.469
Your message gave
me much concern.

543
00:43:57.470 --> 00:43:59.973
Yes. I must admit I
had reason to fear.

544
00:44:02.100 --> 00:44:03.768
But come. see for yourself.

545
00:45:34.025 --> 00:45:36.403
I wasn't expecting you.

546
00:45:38.905 --> 00:45:41.116
That seems rather a
lapse in foresight.

547
00:45:44.369 --> 00:45:48.080
- I see you have done well here.
- They are sworn to me.

548
00:45:48.081 --> 00:45:50.250
And not a moment too soon.

549
00:45:55.130 --> 00:45:57.382
And to whom are you sworn?

550
00:46:54.981 --> 00:46:57.608
The realm's only hope...

551
00:46:57.609 --> 00:46:59.276
is a leader who can unite it

552
00:46:59.277 --> 00:47:02.781
and my brother chose... you.

553
00:47:21.966 --> 00:47:24.177
You are the true
queen. Rhaenyra.

554
00:47:25.178 --> 00:47:27.471
First of Her Name.

555
00:47:27.472 --> 00:47:29.516
Protector of the Realm.

556
00:47:30.183 --> 00:47:34.144
I am meant to serve you.
and all of these with me.

557
00:47:34.145 --> 00:47:36.105
until death

558
00:47:36.106 --> 00:47:38.525
or the end of our story.

559
00:48:28.199 --> 00:48:29.784
My queen.

560
00:48:39.794 --> 00:48:43.172
For every one of us who falls...

561
00:48:43.173 --> 00:48:45.424
a hundred of them!

562
00:48:45.425 --> 00:48:48.553
There will be no mercy!

563
00:48:48.928 --> 00:48:51.513
We fight for our queen!

564
00:49:36.601 --> 00:49:38.770
You sent for me. Lord Hand.

565
00:49:40.605 --> 00:49:42.816
Gulls are flying low today.

566
00:49:43.608 --> 00:49:46.110
The weather will change.

567
00:49:46.111 --> 00:49:48.737
Not until late. I think. but...

568
00:49:48.738 --> 00:49:51.156
- I will ready the storm sails.
- We join the blockade.

569
00:49:51.157 --> 00:49:55.453
and are like to find ourselves
in peril. sooner than late.

570
00:49:56.538 --> 00:50:00.000
I wish to set out on good
terms with my first mate.

571
00:50:00.625 --> 00:50:02.334
Have I been remiss in my duties?

572
00:50:02.335 --> 00:50:05.005
You've done what is
asked of you. and more.

573
00:50:05.839 --> 00:50:09.466
But you are curt... silent.

574
00:50:09.467 --> 00:50:12.512
and the men find you distant.

575
00:50:13.221 --> 00:50:15.807
You cannot lead if
you do not inspire.

576
00:50:16.224 --> 00:50:18.852
Well. I never asked to
lead. as you well know.

577
00:50:21.688 --> 00:50:24.733
You have been given a position to
which all who serve here aspire.

578
00:50:27.318 --> 00:50:29.319
Forgive me. my lord.

579
00:50:29.320 --> 00:50:31.573
I will endeavor
to improve myself.

580
00:50:35.702 --> 00:50:38.163
I am trying to help you.

581
00:50:44.669 --> 00:50:46.171
You want to help me?

582
00:50:48.048 --> 00:50:50.341
Is this the help you offer
after all these years?

583
00:50:50.342 --> 00:50:52.594
A reminder to be grateful?

584
00:50:53.428 --> 00:50:54.846
I mean no offense.

585
00:50:55.680 --> 00:50:56.890
You may go.

586
00:51:00.518 --> 00:51:02.729
Do you know what
it was like for us?

587
00:51:04.022 --> 00:51:06.231
To grow up fatherless...

588
00:51:06.232 --> 00:51:08.233
to be sneered upon as bastards.

589
00:51:08.234 --> 00:51:10.194
never sure of the
bread to feed us?

590
00:51:10.195 --> 00:51:12.572
D-D-Do you know what
hunger does to a boy?

591
00:51:13.615 --> 00:51:15.908
What grief does?

592
00:51:15.909 --> 00:51:18.370
- Or shame?
- You are dismissed.

593
00:51:18.787 --> 00:51:20.996
I sold fish in the market

594
00:51:20.997 --> 00:51:23.749
from cold dawn until sunset.

595
00:51:23.750 --> 00:51:26.251
putting by coppers to
stave off the winter.

596
00:51:26.252 --> 00:51:29.380
and I watched the man
who sired me walk past

597
00:51:29.381 --> 00:51:32.216
with his son and heir

598
00:51:32.217 --> 00:51:35.220
with a fur around
his shoulders...

599
00:51:35.804 --> 00:51:40.809
choosing sweetmeats to eat
after supper by the fire.

600
00:51:42.936 --> 00:51:45.229
And now that boy is dead.

601
00:51:45.230 --> 00:51:47.231
And his sister before him.

602
00:51:47.232 --> 00:51:48.941
And the heir that
took his place.

603
00:51:48.942 --> 00:51:52.612
And now. now. now
you remember I live.

604
00:51:54.114 --> 00:51:56.198
Now you wish to...

605
00:51:56.199 --> 00:51:58.827
suddenly to scatter the
crumbs of your favor.

606
00:52:01.329 --> 00:52:05.417
I am an honorable man. and I
will serve you because I must.

607
00:52:06.001 --> 00:52:08.919
But if it is all the same.

608
00:52:08.920 --> 00:52:13.425
I will decline any
offers of help.

609
00:52:15.468 --> 00:52:17.470
If I survive this war...

610
00:52:17.846 --> 00:52:20.265
I will continue as I began...

611
00:52:22.100 --> 00:52:23.309
alone.

612
00:53:14.652 --> 00:53:18.155
You have done what no
one else would dream of.

613
00:53:18.156 --> 00:53:20.367
and you have been rewarded.

614
00:53:21.076 --> 00:53:23.328
The gods favor you.

615
00:53:24.245 --> 00:53:27.289
They put the means to
victory in your hands.

616
00:53:27.290 --> 00:53:31.502
And yet. to claim
it. I must strike

617
00:53:31.503 --> 00:53:34.963
and in striking. I doom
thousands to their deaths.

618
00:53:39.844 --> 00:53:42.222
I do not believe my father
would've wished this.

619
00:53:43.098 --> 00:53:45.349
He left you with no choice.

620
00:53:45.350 --> 00:53:49.019
Be strong. You
know you are just.

621
00:53:49.020 --> 00:53:50.854
You must not let the
Realm fall to those

622
00:53:50.855 --> 00:53:53.899
who care for power
more than peace.

623
00:53:53.900 --> 00:53:56.194
You must prevail.

624
00:53:59.197 --> 00:54:01.199
And who pays the price?

625
00:54:19.217 --> 00:54:20.426
Come.

626
00:54:24.973 --> 00:54:26.975
Begging your pardon. Your Grace.

627
00:54:40.405 --> 00:54:42.407
I had to see you.

628
00:54:51.249 --> 00:54:53.083
- Who knows?
- None save my protector.

629
00:54:53.084 --> 00:54:55.337
He laid down his
sword at your gate.

630
00:55:05.096 --> 00:55:09.309
I've been. I
think... mistaken.

631
00:55:11.311 --> 00:55:13.604
In what?

632
00:55:13.605 --> 00:55:16.815
I was raised to believe
there was an order to things.

633
00:55:16.816 --> 00:55:21.112
that there was security in
following the paths laid out for us.

634
00:55:21.988 --> 00:55:23.238
I resented you. I think.

635
00:55:23.239 --> 00:55:25.449
for... caring so
little for any of it.

636
00:55:25.450 --> 00:55:28.161
for knowing what you wanted.

637
00:55:28.703 --> 00:55:30.747
I did not know what I wanted.

638
00:55:31.289 --> 00:55:33.458
I knew only what
was expected of me.

639
00:55:36.711 --> 00:55:39.963
- Why have you come here?
- Because I lost my way.

640
00:55:39.964 --> 00:55:42.634
Or rather. it was taken from me.

641
00:55:43.051 --> 00:55:45.135
All those I put
my faith in. my...

642
00:55:45.136 --> 00:55:48.097
- m-my husband. my father. my lover. my son...
- Ooh.

643
00:55:48.098 --> 00:55:49.932
The incorruptible queen

644
00:55:49.933 --> 00:55:51.475
sullies herself with a lover.

645
00:55:51.476 --> 00:55:53.520
Do not judge me for what
you yourself have done.

646
00:55:54.187 --> 00:55:56.898
Your father died. I took
comfort with another.

647
00:55:57.482 --> 00:56:01.151
- I too have desires.
- Yes. but you alone made virtue your banner.

648
00:56:01.152 --> 00:56:04.279
And I clung to it...
in defiance of you.

649
00:56:04.280 --> 00:56:06.908
I think. who so disdained it.

650
00:56:17.836 --> 00:56:20.045
I have been alone. of late.

651
00:56:20.046 --> 00:56:22.339
I walked outside the
walls of the city

652
00:56:22.340 --> 00:56:24.509
and I felt a weight
lifted from me.

653
00:56:24.843 --> 00:56:27.469
- How lovely for you.
- I thought. for the first time.

654
00:56:27.470 --> 00:56:29.514
what I would choose...

655
00:56:30.056 --> 00:56:31.974
if not for the duty I
put before all else.

656
00:56:31.975 --> 00:56:35.853
Shall you cast your son
down and rule alone?

657
00:56:35.854 --> 00:56:38.523
No. I do not wish to
rule. I wish to live.

658
00:56:39.065 --> 00:56:42.651
To be free of all this
endless plotting and striving.

659
00:56:42.652 --> 00:56:44.862
The crown will pursue war
and victory at any cost.

660
00:56:44.863 --> 00:56:48.074
I... But as for me...

661
00:56:49.784 --> 00:56:53.413
I would take my daughter and her
child and leave it all behind.

662
00:56:54.706 --> 00:56:58.376
It's too late... Alicent.

663
00:56:59.627 --> 00:57:02.421
You said it yourself.
Blood has been shed.

664
00:57:02.422 --> 00:57:04.423
cities burned. armies march.

665
00:57:04.424 --> 00:57:06.425
and you wish to wash your hands

666
00:57:06.426 --> 00:57:08.093
of what you yourself
set in motion.

667
00:57:08.094 --> 00:57:09.762
Oh. the arrogance of blaming me.

668
00:57:09.763 --> 00:57:11.555
as if you would not have
been challenged regardless.

669
00:57:11.556 --> 00:57:13.557
Did not your hand bring
it forth like a midwife?

670
00:57:13.558 --> 00:57:16.061
I did only what I thought
your father wanted.

671
00:57:18.229 --> 00:57:19.898
Oh. go then.

672
00:57:21.107 --> 00:57:22.566
Leave us behind. as you say.

673
00:57:22.567 --> 00:57:24.110
Rhaenyra.

674
00:57:24.903 --> 00:57:27.529
Wander in the wilderness.

675
00:57:27.530 --> 00:57:29.574
What has it got to do with me?

676
00:57:33.912 --> 00:57:36.915
Did you come here thinking
you would be absolved?

677
00:57:55.975 --> 00:57:58.603
He never stopped loving
your mother. you know?

678
00:57:59.312 --> 00:58:01.105
He was very fond of
me. and I of him.

679
00:58:01.106 --> 00:58:03.273
but...

680
00:58:03.274 --> 00:58:05.485
she was the vision
that sustained him

681
00:58:06.444 --> 00:58:07.611
even after she herself

682
00:58:07.612 --> 00:58:10.072
had slipped from
his grasp. it was

683
00:58:10.073 --> 00:58:11.824
his love for her that
kept him resolute

684
00:58:11.825 --> 00:58:13.659
in his choice of heir.

685
00:58:13.660 --> 00:58:16.121
And yet. you believe
he wavered at the end.

686
00:58:22.544 --> 00:58:24.546
Why have you come here?

687
00:58:27.298 --> 00:58:30.301
Aemond will soon fly to
join Cole in the Riverlands.

688
00:58:32.637 --> 00:58:34.139
When he's gone...

689
00:58:34.681 --> 00:58:36.932
Helaena as queen will be
the crown's authority.

690
00:58:36.933 --> 00:58:39.143
If you come then to King's
Landing. I will see to it

691
00:58:39.144 --> 00:58:40.936
that our guards throw
down their arms.

692
00:58:40.937 --> 00:58:43.982
we will open the gates.
we will shed no blood.

693
00:58:44.816 --> 00:58:47.402
You will enter as a conqueror.

694
00:58:48.653 --> 00:58:50.655
Already you have
the stronger hand.

695
00:58:51.823 --> 00:58:53.198
Once you take the throne...

696
00:58:53.199 --> 00:58:56.703
this senseless war must end.

697
00:58:59.330 --> 00:59:00.749
Right.

698
00:59:05.003 --> 00:59:06.171
What of Aegon?

699
00:59:13.553 --> 00:59:16.765
He's broken beyond recognition.

700
00:59:18.266 --> 00:59:21.269
He lies in the dark.
in pain and terror.

701
00:59:21.770 --> 00:59:23.396
He has many faults. but...

702
00:59:24.397 --> 00:59:25.647
he still heeds his mother.

703
00:59:25.648 --> 00:59:27.066
I believe I can prevail upon him

704
00:59:27.067 --> 00:59:30.361
- to bend the knee. if indeed...
- No! Still...

705
00:59:30.362 --> 00:59:32.030
you defend him.

706
00:59:33.740 --> 00:59:37.076
Still you imagine you
can have all you want

707
00:59:37.077 --> 00:59:38.577
without paying too high a price.

708
00:59:38.578 --> 00:59:40.871
- a price I had no choice but to pay.
- What I want

709
00:59:40.872 --> 00:59:42.874
is to set things right.

710
00:59:44.918 --> 00:59:46.752
If I am to take the throne.

711
00:59:46.753 --> 00:59:50.089
I must put an end
to the opposition.

712
00:59:50.090 --> 00:59:51.548
I must take Aegon's head.

713
00:59:51.549 --> 00:59:53.509
And I have to do
it for all to see.

714
00:59:53.510 --> 00:59:55.136
You know this.

715
00:59:56.888 --> 00:59:59.724
However you may try to
evade it. you know this.

716
01:00:10.568 --> 01:00:11.778
Choose.

717
01:00:21.287 --> 01:00:24.123
Will you shrink from
what you set out to do?

718
01:00:24.124 --> 01:00:26.167
Or will you see it through...

719
01:00:27.460 --> 01:00:29.129
and make your sacrifice?

720
01:00:34.259 --> 01:00:36.261
A son for a son.

721
01:01:29.397 --> 01:01:31.441
You are much changed.

722
01:01:31.983 --> 01:01:35.153
Let us be done
with this. please.

723
01:01:37.489 --> 01:01:39.908
And what do I do with you now?

724
01:01:41.743 --> 01:01:45.372
You let me go. to
do what I promised.

725
01:01:46.664 --> 01:01:48.874
And you fly to the Red
Keep in three days' time.

726
01:01:48.875 --> 01:01:51.043
and you take your throne.

727
01:01:51.044 --> 01:01:53.338
Or you take me for a liar.

728
01:01:54.255 --> 01:01:55.631
I have neither weapon nor armor.

729
01:01:55.632 --> 01:01:56.965
My life itself is forfeit.

730
01:01:56.966 --> 01:02:00.052
I... cast myself on
the mercy of a friend

731
01:02:00.053 --> 01:02:02.097
who once loved me.

732
01:02:04.015 --> 01:02:05.600
History will paint
you a villain.

733
01:02:09.938 --> 01:02:11.940
A cold queen...

734
01:02:14.526 --> 01:02:17.195
grasping for power.
and then defeated.

735
01:02:17.862 --> 01:02:19.864
Let them think what they must.

736
01:02:22.367 --> 01:02:24.619
I am at last myself...

737
01:02:25.537 --> 01:02:30.125
with no ambition greater than to walk
where I please and to breathe the open air.

738
01:02:32.711 --> 01:02:35.380
To die unremarked
and unnoticed...

739
01:02:36.965 --> 01:02:38.591
and be free.

740
01:02:42.387 --> 01:02:44.764
You speak as if from
a distant dream.

741
01:02:45.724 --> 01:02:47.142
Come with me.

742
01:02:51.146 --> 01:02:55.150
My part is here.
whether I will or no.

743
01:02:56.276 --> 01:02:58.903
It was decided for me long ago.

744
01:03:05.410 --> 01:03:07.245
Go.

745
01:03:08.305 --> 01:04:08.596
